sec.p:
The calculation of the COVID-19 imported risk index assumes that the migrant population conforms to the population distribution in the source region, and the risk of disease is consistent with the incidence rate of the source region. The imported risk of COVID-19 caused by population migration can be expressed by the scale of migration, the number of patients in the source region, and the population. The calculation formula for the imported risk index is as follows:
