				\begin{document}$$ {\mathrm{Risk}}_{in,t}=\sum \left(\frac{{\mathrm{case}}_{i,t}}{{\mathrm{pop}}_i}\times {iMI}_{i,t}\times 1000\right) $$\end{document}Riskin,t=∑casei,tpopi×iMIi,t×1000where Riskin,t represents the imported risk index on day t, casei,t represents the number of new cases in city i on day t, popi represents the population of city i, and iMIi,t represents the population size index of immigration from city i on day t.
